    "gut_harmony_feature_6gkhMK": {
      "type": "gut-harmony-feature",
      "name": "Gut Harmony Feature",
      "settings": {
        "use_theme_colors": false,
        "padding_top": 80,
        "padding_bottom": 80,
        "padding_top_mobile": 40,
        "padding_bottom_mobile": 40,
        "title_gap": 40,
        "column_gap": 24,
        "content_gap": 24,
        "background_color": "#ffffff",
        "title": "The Metabolism–Energy–Desire Connection",
        "title_size": 40,
        "title_size_mobile": 26,
        "title_color": "#3b3b3b",
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/metabolic-flow-45-1908323.webp",
        "image_border_radius": 0,
        "body_text": "<p>Your metabolism does more than influence weight.</p><p>It helps regulate how your body uses food for energy, how steady you feel throughout the day, how often cravings show up, and how efficiently your body supports daily function.</p><p>When metabolic balance changes, women may notice:</p><ul><li>More food noise</li><li>Stronger sugar cravings</li><li>Energy crashes after meals</li><li>Slower digestion</li><li>Less daily vitality</li><li>Feeling mentally and physically drained</li></ul><p>And when your energy is low, your body often prioritizes getting through the day — not feeling vibrant, confident, or connected.</p>",
        "text_size": 16,
        "text_color": "#3b3b3b",
        "testimonial_text": "<p><strong>That’s why supporting metabolism after 45 isn’t just about appearance.</strong></p><p><strong>It’s about helping your body feel supported from the inside.</strong></p>",
        "testimonial_size": 18,
        "testimonial_paragraph_spacing": 12,
        "testimonial_color": "#a9617a",
